                <h1>Understanding the Nazi Regime: History and Impacts</h1>
                <p>The Nazi regime, led by Adolf Hitler from 1933 to 1945, was characterized by totalitarian governance, aggressive nationalism, and extreme anti-Semitism. This era marked devastating consequences, including the Holocaust, which aimed to exterminate the Jewish population and other minorities. The impacts of Nazism still resonate today in discussions around human rights and historical accountability.</p>
